After recording much success with the release of ‘Living in Bondage Breaking Free’ top movie charts and staying among highest ranking movies; Versatile movie maker cum executive producer, Charles Okpaleke have revealed that there is another big project on the line which is the remake of 1994 classic movie ‘ Glamour Girls’ scheduled for a grand premiere come December 2021. Sharing the great news, Charles through an Instagram post revealed that the upcoming ‘Glamour Girls’ will focus on three generations of actresses. ‘A story that would involve 3 generations of female actresses. I’m going all out on this one”, said Okpaleke. It will be recalled that the 1994 classic, directed by Chika Onukwufor, follows the tale of four women who resort to high profile prostitution in order to lead more independent lives. ‘Glamour Girls’ made the careers of Nollywood veterans like Eucharia Anunobi, Zack Orji, Liz Benson, Dolly Unachukwu, Gloria Alozie, Ernest Obi, Ngozi Ezeonu, Gloria Anozie, Pat Attah and Sandra Achums.